    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The lighting model implemented by "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is identical to the lighting model implemented in OpenGL ES 1.1; each light interacts with any material properties on the effect to determine the intensity and color that particular light contributes to the scene at a fragment."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "There are three basic kinds of lights: directional, point and spotlights."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A directional light is considered to be infinitely far away, and always directs light in the same direction. To create a directional light, set the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473576-position"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property to a vector whose "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "x"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "y"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "z"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " components specify the direction to the light (that is, the negation of the direction the light is travelling in), and whose "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "w"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " component is set to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "0.0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A point light is placed at a position within the scene, and emits light in all directions. To create a directional light, set the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473576-position"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property to a vector whose "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "x"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "y"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "z"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "w"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " components specify the homogenous coordinates for the position of the light in the scene. The "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "w"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " component is typically set to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "1.0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and must not be set to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "0.0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The intensity of a point light is adjusted using an distance attenuation function. This function is controlled by adjusting the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473574-constantattenuation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473549-linearattenuation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " or "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473578-quadraticattenuation"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " properties. The default values for these properties create a light whose intensity is constant over distance."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A spotlight is placed at a position within the scene, and emits light in a specific direction in a cone. To create a spotlight, set the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473576-position"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property to a vector whose "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "x"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "y"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "z"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "w"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " components specify the homogenous coordinates for the position of the light in the scene. The "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "w"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " component must not be set to "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "codeVoice",
                      "code": "0.0"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ". Then, set the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/glkit/glkeffectpropertylight/1473547-spotdirection"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " property to a vector that specifies the direction of the light and the "
                    },
                    {
